HEADWORD: Spectroheliogram
<hw>Spec`tro*he"li*o*gram`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Spectrum</ets> + <ets>heloi-</ets> + <ets>-gram</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Astrophysics)</fld> <def>A photograph of the sun made by
monochromatic light, usually of the calcium line (k), and showing the
sun's faculae and prominences.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

